commit.message:
Merge pull request #67 from aprildh31/patch-1

Fixed Spelling/Grammar Error

Fixed Spelling/Grammar Error

Changed "loose" (adjective) to "lose" (verb).

Drop support for older readline versions

Signed-off-by: Sebastian Ramacher <sebastian+dev@ramacher.at>

Fix xdiff alias

You cannot use aliases (such as "lrm") in aliases.

I've been using this alias for ages and only realised when adding
into the default yafcrc that the temp file wasn't getting
cleared. In my haste, I added the lrm without testing first.
Sorry about that.

Add two aliases for useful commands

xcd
	Change both local and remote directory at the same time

xdiff
	Diff local and remote file
	Very useful prior to updating a configuration file

Fix some cppcheck errors

Signed-off-by: Sebastian Ramacher <sebastian+dev@ramacher.at>
Bump version number
Update NEWS
Update copyright years

Fix warning

Signed-off-by: Sebastian Ramacher <sebastian+dev@ramacher.at>

Run update-po

Signed-off-by: Sebastian Ramacher <sebastian+dev@ramacher.at>

Fix format string warnings

Signed-off-by: Sebastian Ramacher <sebastian+dev@ramacher.at>

Merge pull request #65 from fluks/set-dodumentation

Add set command documentation
Add set command documentation

Merge pull request #64 from fluks/bash-complete-options

Complete options

Complete options

Add completion of options.

If there are aliases in bookmarks and none of the arguments is an
alias, try to complete an alias. If there are no aliases in bookmarks
or alias is one of the arguments, do the default completion.

Merge pull request #62 from fluks/switch-bug

Fix switch when disconnected

Fix switch when disconnected

Using the command "switch name", segfaults when there are no open
connections. Make sure Ftp struct's url field is not NULL, before
checking whether the name matches a connection.

Merge pull request #61 from fluks/double-free-bug

Fix double free bug

Fix double free bug

Fix parsing of a command string "; ;", which causes a double free.

Merge pull request #59 from fluks/justify-date

Justify date in ls -l

Justify date in ls -l

On some locales the length of the shortened month names can vary.
Calling ls -l, the date strings are not justified correctly. Fix this by
finding the longest date string and justifying on it.
Also check 504 return code

Only use STOU for nohup if it is supported (fixes #57)

STOU is still tried, but STOR is used as fallback.

Signed-off-by: Sebastian Ramacher <sebastian+dev@ramacher.at>
Fix parsing of mode (fixes #55)

Bash completion fixed for OSX

OSX's sed doesn't have the -r flag, but has a roughly equivalent called
-E.

On the road to 1.3.6

Signed-off-by: Sebastian Ramacher <sebastian+dev@ramacher.at>
